'''Juriën Godfried Juan Gaari''' (born 23 December 1993) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] for Saudi club [[Abha Club|Abha]]. Born in the Netherlands, he plays for the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].<ref name = "WF">{{Worldfootball.net|jurien-gaari|new_id=pe343890}}</ref>

==Club career==
Gaari played in youth departments of amateur clubs De Musschen and Overmaas Rotterdam before joining the amateur section of [[SBV Excelsior|Excelsior]]. He left the club in 2012 to play for [[VV Smitshoek]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Feenstra |first1=Richard |title=Julien Gaari (Smitshoek) naar Kozakken Boys |url=https://www.voetbalrotterdam.nl/2014/02/julien-gaari-smitshoek-naar-kozakken-boys/ |publisher=Voetbal Rotterdam |access-date=23 September 2020 |language=nl |date=25 February 2014}}</ref> Between 2012 and 2014, he was a regular starter for the club and made a [[KNVB Cup]] appearance against [[NAC Breda]], among other things.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Feenstra |first1=Richard |title=Smitshoek verlaat met opgegeven hoofd de KNVB Beker |url=https://www.voetbalrotterdam.nl/2013/09/smitshoek-verlaat-met-opgegeven-hoofd-de-knvb-beker/ |publisher=Voetbal Rotterdam |access-date=23 September 2020 |date=26 September 2013 |quote=Smitshoek speelde met respect voor de tegenstander, maar zonder ontzag. Dit resulteerde in een aantrekkelijke wedstrijd, waarbij vooral de backs Thijs Oomsen en Jurien Gaari in positieve zin opvielen.}}</ref> He later played for [[Kozakken Boys]], where he quickly became a permanent starter.

After four seasons and a promotion, Gaari joined professional club [[RKC Waalwijk]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=van Velthoven |first1=Florian |title=Laatbloeier Juriën Gaari schittert nu in het profvoetbal bij RKC Waalwijk: 'Droom die uitkomt' |url=https://www.omroepbrabant.nl/nieuws/2864647/laatbloeier-jurien-gaari-schittert-nu-in-het-profvoetbal-bij-rkc-waalwijk-droom-die-uitkomt |publisher=Omroep Brabant |access-date=23 September 2020 |language=nl |date=12 October 2018}}</ref> He made his debut for the first team on 17 August 2018, in a 1&ndash;0 home win over [[SC Telstar|Telstar]].

After his contract with Waalwijk expired, Gaari joined [[Saudi Second Division League|Saudi Second Division]] club [[Al-Hazem FC|Al-Hazem]].<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Elst |first1=Maarten |last2=van Wanrooij |first2=Jurre |date=2024-08-23 |title=Na 169 wedstrijden in het shirt van RKC vindt rechtsachter Gaari nieuwe club |url=https://www.bd.nl/rkc-waalwijk/na-169-wedstrijden-in-het-shirt-van-rkc-vindt-rechtsachter-gaari-nieuwe-club~a85f9ad5/ |access-date=2025-11-24 |website=bd.nl}}</ref>

On 6 August 2025, Gaari joined [[Saudi First Division League]] side [[Abha Club|Abha]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Welcome Juriën Gaari |url=https://x.com/abhaFC/status/1953151979863355580}}</ref>

==International career==

He played for Curaçao at the [[2017 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2017]] and [[2019 CONCACAF Gold Cup|2019]] [[CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/jurien-gaari/315769/|title=Curaçao – J. Gaari – Profile with news, career statistics and history – Soccerway|website=int.soccerway.com}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Curaçao on June 25, 2019 in the latter tournament against [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]], a late equalizer that gave the team a 1-1 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://matchcenter.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter/2019-06-25-jamaica-vs-curacao/recap|date=June 25, 2019|first=Ian|last=Quillen|title=Jamaica 1, Curacao 1 - 2019 Concacaf Gold Cup Match Recap|access-date=2019-06-26|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030224431/https://matchcenter.mlssoccer.com/matchcenter/2019-06-25-jamaica-vs-curacao/recap|url-status=dead}}</ref>

